                     <p> BURTON. Condition of a bond by which <persName>
                           <forename>John</forename> 
                           <surname>Staynton</surname>
                        </persName> 
                  is bound in Â£100 to <persName>
                           <forename>Laurence</forename> 
                           <surname>Kay</surname>
                        </persName> that if he do not pay 
                  a sum of 18 marks at the feast of St. John the Baptist next, then he shall make a feoffment of all the lands which 
                  were <persName>
                           <forename>William</forename> 
                           <surname>Perot</surname>
                        </persName>'s in <placeName key="place_103370">Thornby</placeName> 
                  in the parish of <placeName key="place_103101">Byrton</placeName> for 24 marks.
                  Dated 11 March, <origDate notBefore="1433-09-01" notAfter="1434-08-31">12 Henry VI</origDate>. 
